Carthage support

This commit adds a .xcodeproj which includes all the files from the
library.
It also sets the scheme of the newly created Xcode project to “Shared”
in order for carthage to build a .framework.
It also adds a .gitignore file, ignoring the recommended files
generated by Xcode
Newly added property for KVO usage: maybe you only want to observe the local network is available or not.

optimization around the using of pingFoundation object; no longer hold the object all the time, create once before every ping request.

IPV6 support;
APPLE: Starting June 1, 2016 all apps submitted to the App Store must support IPv6-only networking.
https://developer.apple.com/news/?id=05042016a
So this lib should be upgraded to support IPV6 now.  Found any issue around IPV6, contact me. Thank you!
